actions.text: The House Committee on Rules reported an original measure, H. Rept. 102-967, by Mr. Beilenson.
Rule provides for consideration of the conference report to H.R. 5095. Waiving all points of order against the conference report and against its consideration in the House.
Placed on the House Calendar, Calendar No. 221.
DEBATE - The House proceeded with one hour of debate.
The previous question was ordered without objection.
On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to by the Yeas and Nays: 399 - 2 (Roll No. 451).
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

official_title: Waiving points of order against the conference report to accompany the bill (H.R. 5095) to authorize appropriations for fiscal year 1993 for intelligence and intelligence-related activities of the United States Government and the Central Intelligence Agency Retirement and Disability System, and for other purposes.

summary.text: Waives points of order against the consideration of the conference report on H.R. 5095 (intelligence activities funding).
